resources.name: Detailed information on public opinion website

description:
This public opinion survey was carried out at the request of the Directorate-General for Health and Consumer Protection and was managed and organised by the Public Opinion Analysis Unit of the Press and Communication Service.
1. Smoking in the European Union 
1.1. Smoking Habits 
Smoking Habits: Comparison with 1995 
Socio-demographic profiles 
1.2. Frequency of Smoking: Number of Cigarettes/Day
1.3. Light Cigarettes 
1.4. Smoking in Public Places 
Asking Smokers not to Smoke
Respecting Smoking Regulations 
1.5. Warnings about Impact of Smoking on Health 
2. Attitudes Toward the Environment and Health in the European Union
2.1. Environmental Factors and Impact Upon Health
Impact of Noise Upon Health
2.2. Overall Health
2.3. Environmental Action
Willingness to Carry Out Environmentally Friendly Actions
2.4. Health Risks Linked to the Environment 
2.5. Public Bodies and Protection from Health Risks 
2.6. Information on Environmentally-Linked Health Risks
2.7. Trust of Sources 
It was conducted in all the Member at States of the European Union between October 28 and December 8, 2002, under the general coordination of the European Opinion Research Group EEIG. in Brussels.
#####The results by volumes are distributed as follows:
* Volume A: Countries
* Volume AA: Groups of countries
* Volume A' (AP): Trends
* Volume AA' (AAP): Trends of groups of countries
* Volume B: EU/socio-demographics
* Volume C: Country/socio-demographics
title: Special Eurobarometer 183: Smoking & Health/Environment & Health
